said...
</dt>
<dd class='comment-body' id='Blog1_cmt-789831132030446361'>
<p>
Although Lulu could probably be called a vanity press, they do make the process very easy for an author with a limited budget and limited audience. For example, a former English teacher of mine published her book on Lulu and has made about $500 so far selling it to friends and former students. However, on a fixed income she couldn&#39;t afford to pay upfront for the printing, so she was willing to take a smaller cut of the profits. CreateSpace was just getting started then, and I have been very impressed with their offerings, as well.
</p>
</dd>
